components.name: Extract Vendor Shipments
components.description: Reads raw shipment CSV files from three vendors and passes the extracted data via XCom for downstream processing.

components.name: Cleanse and Normalize Shipments
components.description: Combines extracted vendor data, normalizes SKU formats, validates dates, filters invalid records, and enriches shipments with location reference data.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after all three vendor extraction tasks have succeeded

components.name: Load Shipments to Inventory Database
components.description: Writes the cleansed shipment data into the inventory_shipments table of the PostgreSQL inventory database.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful data cleansing and normalization

components.name: Send ETL Summary Email
components.description: Sends a daily email summary to the supply chain team after successful loading of shipment data.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered only after the database load completes successfully

connections.purpose: SMTP server for sending ETL summary notifications

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

sources: Vendor shipment CSV files (vendor_a_shipments_20240115.csv, vendor_b_shipments_20240115.csv, vendor_c_shipments_20240115.csv) stored on a shared filesystem
Location reference tables used for enrichment (e.g., location_reference_table.csv)
sinks: PostgreSQL inventory_shipments table in the inventory_db database
Daily ETL summary email sent to supply-chain-team@company.com
intermediate_datasets: XCom payloads: vendor_a_data, vendor_b_data, vendor_c_data (raw extracted records)
XCom payload: cleansed_shipment_data (combined, normalized, and enriched records)
